## 1. Working conventions (prevent repeated mistakes)

- **Delivering files:** generate → `present_files` → lands in `$HOME\Downloads` →
  give a PowerShell block to move into the repo. Overwrites: back up first with a
  timestamped `.bak-<stamp>` next to the original.
- **PowerShell gotchas hit this session:**
  - `[id]` folders need `-LiteralPath` (brackets are wildcards otherwise).
  - Recursive greps over the whole tree hang on `node_modules` — always prune it.
  - The Supabase SQL editor **swallows `RAISE NOTICE`** output and runs without a
    JWT, so owner-gated RPCs reject and reversible `DO`-block tests can't show
    results. Verify money/stock changes **through the real UI** as the logged-in
    owner instead.
  - Owner-gated RPCs in the SQL editor need a JWT claim first, run in the SAME
    batch: `set local request.jwt.claims = '{"sub":"3f135a05-...","role":"authenticated"}';`
    then the call.
  - i18n dictionary (`lib/i18n/dictionary.ts`) has EN (~line 342) and ES (~line
    675) blocks with identical ASCII anchors; patch the second occurrence first
    (by index) so the first index stays valid. Avoid accented anchors.

