## 3. Money-system facts worth keeping

- Money in CENTS (bigint). Movements all live in the `transactions` table
  (there is NO separate movements table). `account_statement(account_id)` RPC
  builds the per-account statement; it does NO currency conversion — it reads
  `amount_cents` raw, so the amount must be stored in the account's own currency.
- `transactions.source_*` columns tag the movement type (purchase_order, sale,
  sale_payment, transfer, commission_payout, courier_payment).
- Stored `balance_cents` can drift from computed (opening + sum movements);
  `set_account_opening` re-syncs it. The Movimientos modal shows an amber drift
  note when stored ≠ computed.

